<em>Timaeus</em>,&rdquo; <em>Antichthon</em>, 13: 19&ndash;29.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2004, &ldquo;Must commentators know their
sources? Proclus in <em>Timaeum</em> and Numenius&rdquo;, in P.
Adamson, H. Balthussen, M. Stone (eds.), <em>Philosophy, science and
exegesis in Greek, Arabic and Latin commentaries</em> (Volumes
I&ndash;II), <em>Bulletin of the Institute of Classical Studies</em>,
83(1&ndash;2): 175&ndash;190.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2015, &ldquo;The <em>Phaedo</em> in
Numenian Allegorical Interpretation&rdquo;, in S. Delcomminette, P.
d&rsquo;Hoine, M.-A. Gavray (eds.), <em>Ancient Readings of
Plato&rsquo;s Phaedo</em>, Leiden: Brill, 134&ndash;153.</li>

<li>Ulacco, A., 2017, <em>Pseudopythagorica Dorica. I trattati di
argomento metafisico, logico ed epistemologico attribuiti ad Archita e
a Brotino</em>, Berlin/Boston: De Gruyter.</li>

<li>Waszink, J. H., 1966, &ldquo;Porphyrius und Numenius,&rdquo; in
<em>Porphyre</em>, Entretiens Fondation Hardt 12,
Vandoeuvres-Gen&egrave;ve, 35&ndash;78.</li>

<li>Whittaker, J., 1967, &ldquo;Moses Atticizing&rdquo;,
<em>Phoenix</em>, 21: 196&ndash;201.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1984, &ldquo;Numenius and Alcinous on the
First Principle&rdquo;, <em>Phoenix</em>, 32: 144&ndash;154.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1987, &ldquo;Platonic Philosophy in the
Early Centuries of the Empire&rdquo;, in <em>Aufstieg und Niedergang
der r&ouml;mischen Welt</em>, 36(1): 81&ndash;123.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1993, &ldquo;Numenius&rsquo; fragment 2 and
the literary tradition&rdquo;, <em>Symbolae Osloenses</em>, 68:
96&ndash;99.</li>

<li>Zambon, M., 2002, <em>Porphyre et le Moyen-Platonisme</em>, Paris:
Vrin.</li>
</ul>
</div> 

